external_knowledge:
- "blooming flowers" metaphorically refers to the candidates who are present;
- "garden of examinations" symbolizes the location or context of the examination schedules;
- "seeds of presence" metaphorically refers to the 'Present' attendance status indicating the candidates who attended.

- "Rising stars" metaphorically refers to the top-performing candidates;
- "Golden tickets" symbolizes the achievement of securing a position within the top ten;
- "Exam type 1" specifies the particular examination under consideration;
- "Unveil their identities" means to reveal the names and application numbers of the candidates;
- "Precious rank" denotes the competitive ranking achieved by the candidate;
- "Result status" represents the final certification or outcome of their participation in the exam.

sql:
SELECT name, email
FROM candidates
WHERE candidate_id > 5;

SELECT * 
FROM examination_schedules
CROSS JOIN notifications;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_attendees
FROM candidate_examination_schedules
WHERE attendance_status = 'Present';

